      • processFrame

        public org.opencv.core.Mat processFrame​(org.opencv.core.Mat input)
        This function takes the RGB frame, converts to YCrCb, and extracts the Y channel to the 'Y' variable, and also creates the submats of each rectangle (A,B,C). Then, it takes the average values of the Y on each mat as an analysis. It subsequently releases the mats in memory to prevent leakage. It decides which barcode the duck is on by finding the two with the smallest difference, then choosing the third.
        Specified by:
        processFrame in class org.openftc.easyopencv.OpenCvPipeline
        Parameters:
        input - the Mat that is provided by the OpenCV subsystem.
        Returns:
        the input mat with rectangles representing the three barcode areas drawn on it.
